# 🐳 Run Nginx in Docker

## ✅ 1. Pull the Official Nginx Image
```bash
docker pull nginx
```

---

## ✅ 2. Run Nginx Container

### Basic:
```bash
docker run --name nginx-container -d -p 8080:80 nginx
```

- `--name nginx-container`: Name your container
- `-d`: Detached mode (runs in background)
- `-p 8080:80`: Maps localhost:8080 to container's port 80

> 🧪 Visit [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080) to see the default Nginx page

---

## ✅ 3. Serve Your Own Files

### On Windows:
```bash
docker run --name nginx-container -d -p 8080:80 -v C:\your\site\folder:/usr/share/nginx/html:ro nginx
```

### On Linux/macOS:
```bash
docker run --name nginx-container -d -p 8080:80 -v $(pwd)/site:/usr/share/nginx/html:ro nginx
```

---

## ✅ 4. Control Nginx Container

```bash
docker stop nginx-container
docker start nginx-container
```

---

## ✅ 5. View Logs

```bash
docker logs nginx-container
```

